    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Material property and contact stiffness sensitivity analysis — non-cannulated construct",
    "description": "One-at-a-time and Morris screening analyses were conducted varying cortical bone modulus (±15%), titanium alloy yield strength (±8%), and rod-screw interface contact stiffness (±25%). Construct stiffness QoI showed less than 4% variation across all parameter perturbations; force at 40 mm displacement varied by up to 7.1%, remaining within the pre-established 10% acceptance bound. Contact stiffness was identified as the dominant sensitivity driver and was subsequently characterised with tighter bounds from coupon-level friction testing."
  },
  "hasContextOfUse": {
